NAME
     update-connector-work-security-map - modifies a  work  secu-
     rity map for the specified resource adapter

SYNOPSIS
     update-connector-work-security-map
     [--help]
       --raname  resource-adapter-name
      [ --addprincipals eis-principal1=server-principal1[, eis-principal2=server-principal2]*]
     [--addusergroups eis-group1=server-group1[, eis-group2=server-group2]*]
      [--removeprincipals eis-principal1[,eis-principal2]*]
      [--removeusergroups eis-group1[, eis-group2]* ]
      work-security-map-name

DESCRIPTION
     Use this command to modify a security map for the  specified
     resource adapter.

     This command is supported in remote mode only.

OPTIONS
     --help

         Displays the help text for the subcommand.

     --addprincipals
         Specifies a comma-separated list of EIS-specific princi-
         pals  to be added. Use either the --addprincipals option
         or the --addgroups option, but not both.

     --addusergroups

         Specifies a comma-separated list of  EIS  groups  to  be
         added.  Use  either the --addprincipals option or the --
         addgroups option, but not both.

     --removeprincipals
         Specifies a comma-separated list of EIS-specific princi-
         palsto  be  removed.  Use  either the --removeprincipals
         option or the --removeusergroups option, but not both.

     --removeusergroups

         Specifies a comma-separated list of  EIS  groups  to  be
         removed. Use either the --removeprincipals option or the
         --removeusergroups option, but not both.

